Interface SeekableObjectSource<T,P>

Type Parameters:
T - The type of object that the implementing class will provide.
All Superinterfaces:
ObjectSource<T>, Seekable<P>
All Known Implementing Classes:
Chunk, ForwardingSeekableObjectSource
public interface SeekableObjectSource<T,P>
extends ObjectSource<T>, Seekable<P>

Defines a source of objects of some type T data that is can be access in some form of random access.

The interface allows data to be iterated in an undefined but deterministic order. It is entirely agnostic in terms of actual source of data.
